From 440eb39082ab62094396a4e836db698897db9e08 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Tesarik <ptesarik@suse.com>
Date: Thu, 3 Apr 2025 16:11:25 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 037/299] FROMLIST: LoongArch: Remove a bogus reference to
 ZONE_DMA

Remove dead code. LoongArch does not have a DMA memory zone. The
architecture does not even define MAX_DMA_PFN.

Signed-off-by: Petr Tesarik <ptesarik@suse.com>
Reviewed-by: Mike Rapoport (Microsoft) <rppt@kernel.org>

Link: https://lore.kernel.org/all/20250403141125.271047-1-ptesarik@suse.com/
Signed-off-by: Kexy Biscuit <kexybiscuit@aosc.io>
---
 arch/loongarch/mm/init.c | 3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/loongarch/mm/init.c b/arch/loongarch/mm/init.c
index fdb7f73ad160..06f11d9e4ec1 100644
--- a/arch/loongarch/mm/init.c
+++ b/arch/loongarch/mm/init.c
@@ -65,9 +65,6 @@ void __init paging_init(void)
 {
 	unsigned long max_zone_pfns[MAX_NR_ZONES];
 
-#ifdef CONFIG_ZONE_DMA
-	max_zone_pfns[ZONE_DMA] = MAX_DMA_PFN;
-#endif
 #ifdef CONFIG_ZONE_DMA32
 	max_zone_pfns[ZONE_DMA32] = MAX_DMA32_PFN;
 #endif
-- 
